The paper deals with identifying important subnetworks in two-mode networks, which is a topic related to social networks, data science, and machine learning. Therefore, cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) and cs.SD (Sound and Music Computing) are the most likely sub-categories. The paper also discusses the algorithmic complexity of the proposed method, which suggests that it could be relevant to cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms). Additionally, the paper presents results obtained from real-life data, which could be of interest to researchers in cs.SOC (Social and Economic Networks) and cs.LG (Machine Learning).
